    "recipeIngredient": [
        "2 pounds bacon (chopped)",
        "2 large onions (finely chopped)",
        "1/2 cup brown sugar",
        "2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar",
        "1/4 tablespoon chili powder",
        "1/4 teaspoon curry powder",
        "Dash cayenne pepper",
        "Splash of coffee",
        "Dash salt",
        "Dash pepper",
        "1 ounce whiskey (optional)"
    ],
    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/119ezP1Ad1vLJj0Eer0yUBCpTa0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-step-01-92a10b731c404e2db10c43307f3abe30.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Gather the ingredients."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/JsiD_tvp77k1KEHvqOQdmCLPJE0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-step-02-2ecda6a73f1f4498b04e25d29fdd8432.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "In a medium-sized sauté pan , cook the bacon over medium heat until the fat has rendered out and the bacon is almost crisp."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/5Zh4FKEU0s_PraenGcfq2ljqMXU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-step-03-e941c755938b43069802cbcd280f1f5d.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Remove cooked bacon, leaving the grease in the pan."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/sZhsyck7j5E5A1fNZsKBtPgkQyk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-step-04-a7555383a8ba482b9cc46cf297364d26.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add onions and sauté until caramelized and soft—about 15 minutes."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/VkdErPY6yTJ98aoccHcMAyoVWsE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-step-05-145ae55a166c4c47b95cbe66b9541fa3.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add chopped crispy bacon back to the onions and stir in brown sugar."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/WI5lWQn4V8OieA_6zPaEanXuLZ8=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-step-06-6ba7832cf6b14d1a92e6e1ccdec2bd18.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add vinegar, chili powder, cayenne pepper, coffee, curry powder, and salt and pepper and cook on low for for at least an hour in a half or until a thick jam forms."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/gwgxwfbO7iXJjQ3PdljVQX8I6kY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-step-07-4a2886e48f7b425faf9ee76824e4676d.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Using a handheld immersion blender , gently pulse the bacon jam until it's mostly creamy with a few chunks of bacon left."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/j5QRh3GmUAeF8mzjiZIVoBw6IVQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/bacon-jam-2937725-hero-02-892909d1f1ce47beb08504aaa5d1c3ab.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Enjoy!"
        }
    ],
    "recipeYield": "32",
    "totalTime": "PT195M",
    "review": [
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "SBaker"
            },
            "reviewBody": "So disappointed! Two pounds of bacon wasted. I only used about half the rendered bacon fat, and it was still way too much. Never coalesced into a jam, after blending everything it separated in a pool of grease lumps of mushy bacon and onions. It was far too oily to use for anything."
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "BARRY Miller"
            },
            "reviewBody": "That is a very great lot of rendered bacon drippings to be leaving in this. I do a beer and bacon jam and remove the greater portion of the rendered bacon drippings. (I know, RBD is a couple of extra syllables that bacon grease, but, it isn't grease! Grease is what you use to lube mechanical gears!)"
        }
    ],
